Part of the story; <br>
Senator, Fred Thompson accused President Clinton's re-election team yesterday of &quot;total manipulation&quot; of the campaign-finance system, saying Mr. Clinton's videotaped political appearances only reinforce the need for an independent counsel. <br>
. . . . The Tennessee Republican hosted a matinee of filmed highlights as the Senate Governmental Affairs Committee watched White House videotapes of fund-raising events showing the president fraternizing with key figures in the finance scandal, dining with donors, and openly crediting a Democratic Party ad blitz with boosting his re-election prospects.<br>
. . . . The problem, Republican critics said, is not the campaign ads themselves, but how they were financed and for what purpose they were developed.<br>
. . . . Mr. Clinton and his political aides &quot;found a way to have their cake and eat it, too,&quot; said Mr. Thompson, chairman of the Senate panel.<br>
Why, I think he ought to be our next president.<br>

